premise_source_doc_sentence: Jeff Bezos  (  -LSB- ˈbeɪzoʊs -RSB- born Jeffrey Preston Jorgensen ; January 12 , 1964  )  is an American technology and retail entrepreneur , investor , and philanthropist who is best known as the founder , chairman , and chief executive officer of Amazon.com , which is the world 's largest online shopping retailer .
The company began as an Internet merchant of books and expanded to a wide variety of products and services , most recently video streaming and audio streaming .

Amazon.com is currently the world 's largest Internet sales company on the World Wide Web , as well as being the world 's largest provider of cloud infrastructure services , through its Amazon Web Services arm .
Bezos 's other diversified business interests include aerospace and newspapers .
He is the founder and manufacturer of Blue Origin  (  founded in 2000  )  with test flights to space which started in 2015 , and plans for commercial suborbital human spaceflight beginning in 2018 .
In 2013 , Bezos purchased The Washington Post newspaper .
A number of other business investments are managed through Bezos Expeditions .

With an estimated net worth of US$ 82 billion as of May 2017 , Bezos is currently the third-richest person in the world , just behind Bill Gates and Amancio Ortega in first and second places , and just ahead of Warren Buffett in fourth place .
His rise to this position occurred after Amazon registered a 67 % jump in share price .
